# Android Best Practices (Kotlin / Jetpack Compose)

Adapted for ShareWind stack: Kotlin, Jetpack Compose, Hilt, Coil, DataStore. See [project-overview.mdc](project-overview.mdc) and [compose-patterns.mdc](compose-patterns.mdc) for architecture and UI patterns.

## Image Loading — Coil

Use **Coil** for all remote images. Never load bitmaps manually or use `BitmapFactory` directly.

```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD — Coil with placeholder and error
AsyncImage(
    model = ImageRequest.Builder(context)
        .data(imageUrl)
        .crossfade(true)
        .build(),
    contentDescription = null,
    modifier = Modifier.fillMaxWidth(),
    placeholder = painterResource(R.drawable.placeholder),
    error = painterResource(R.drawable.error_placeholder)
)
```

## Context Leaks

Avoid holding strong references to `Activity` or `Fragment` in long-lived objects. Use `ApplicationContext` when a long-lived context is needed.

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD — static Context leaks Activity
object BadManager {
    var context: Context? = null
}

// ✅ GOOD — ApplicationContext for long-lived needs
class GoodManager(context: Context) {
    private val appContext = context.applicationContext
}
```

## Security

### Network Security Config

Enforce HTTPS. Disable cleartext in production. Use `network_security_config.xml`:

```xml
<!-- res/xml/network_security_config.xml -->
<network-security-config>
    <base-config cleartextTrafficPermitted="false">
        <trust-anchors>
            <certificates src="system" />
        </trust-anchors>
    </base-config>
    <!-- debug-overrides only for dev if needed -->
</network-security-config>
```

Reference in `AndroidManifest.xml`:
```xml
<application android:networkSecurityConfig="@xml/network_security_config" ...>
```

### Content Providers

If using ContentProviders, set `android:exported="false"` unless explicitly required for sharing.

## Lint

Treat lint warnings as errors. Configure in `build.gradle.kts`:

```kotlin
android {
    lint {
        abortOnError = true
        warningsAsErrors = true
    }
}
```

## Background Work

- **Immediate, short-lived:** Use Kotlin Coroutines (`launch`, `async`) — never block the main thread
- **Deferrable, guaranteed:** Use **WorkManager** for uploads, sync, or scheduled tasks

```kotlin
// WorkManager for deferrable work
val workRequest = OneTimeWorkRequestBuilder<UploadWorker>()
    .setConstraints(Constraints.Builder().setRequiredNetworkType(NetworkType.CONNECTED).build())
    .build()
WorkManager.getInstance(context).enqueue(workRequest)
```

## Testing

- **Unit tests (JVM):** ViewModels, use cases, repositories with mocked dependencies. Use `kotlinx-coroutines-test` for `runTest`.
- **Compose UI tests:** Use `@ComposeTestRule` and `composeTest` for UI flows. Avoid Espresso for Compose screens.
- **Integration tests:** Use `androidTest` for API or DataStore integration when needed.

```kotlin
// ViewModel unit test pattern
@Test
fun `loadRides returns success`() = runTest {
    coEvery { repository.getRides() } returns Result.success(emptyList())
    viewModel.loadRides()
    assertEquals(UiState.Success(emptyList()), viewModel.uiState.value)
}
```
